underlying_goal: Commit and push a large set of related but distinct changes into logically grouped commits.
primary_success: Automatically analyzed a large set of untracked files and split them into four logical, well-documented commits.
brief_summary: The user initiated a commit. The agent analyzed numerous untracked files, identified four distinct logical groups of changes (a new detection module, documentation, configs, and an ignore file), and created four separate, well-described commits. After user confirmation, the agent pushed the commits to the remote branch.
